                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "One thing I like about Lisp syntax is that it has “scoping” built in. I’m using OhmJS a lot and finding that I’m using “+” and “*” less and recursion more. OTOH, I’ve been taking Forth Haiku apart ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/feelingofcomputing.slack.com\/archives\/CCL5VVBAN\/p1772568421543419"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") and marvelling at how concatenative languages can make building compilers very simple."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
